&gt;&gt; Evelyn Rophael: No, self-taught.

00:48:30.870 --> 00:48:34.130
Self-taught, which is not
always the best teacher.

00:48:34.130 --> 00:48:35.430
Anyone else?

00:48:35.430 --> 00:48:36.730
Yes.

00:48:36.730 --> 00:48:55.600
&gt;&gt; Thank you very much
for this presentation.

00:48:55.600 --> 00:49:01.090
It's fascinating.

00:49:01.090 --> 00:49:02.390
[inaudible].

00:49:02.390 --> 00:49:10.080
These are not standard paintings.

00:49:10.080 --> 00:49:16.180
So they're different from what
a standard painting would be.

00:49:16.180 --> 00:49:17.480
[inaudible]?

00:49:17.480 --> 00:49:20.290
&gt;&gt; Evelyn Rophael: Well, first
of all, it's technically,

00:49:20.290 --> 00:49:22.820
you're writing an icon
that, you know,

00:49:22.820 --> 00:49:24.840
because of the Greek
word iconography,

00:49:24.840 --> 00:49:29.380
it actually means writing a
picture, and that picture,

00:49:29.380 --> 00:49:32.950
especially since you're writing
it, you're telling a story.

00:49:32.950 --> 00:49:42.370 position:56%
You're telling a story either of a
saint or a holy scene, and so to me,

00:49:43.760 --> 00:49:53.010
you want to show the person in
the icon as brave and good-looking

00:49:53.010 --> 00:49:56.190
or beautiful, because
that's what their soul is.

00:49:56.190 --> 00:50:02.780
And I want that -- the viewer
to look at an icon and say,

00:50:02.780 --> 00:50:05.160
yes, I'm seeing a story here.

00:50:05.160 --> 00:50:08.360
I don't want them to look at
it and say, that's not pretty.

00:50:08.360 --> 00:50:10.960
So to me, it has to be attractive.

00:50:10.960 --> 00:50:14.660
It has to have symbols in it.

00:50:14.660 --> 00:50:17.360
Almost everything in
the background is going

00:50:17.360 --> 00:50:20.810
to have either three
symbolizing the Holy Trinity

00:50:20.810 --> 00:50:28.650
or four symbolizing the Gospels or
seven, the days of creation, or 12,

00:50:28.650 --> 00:50:37.410
the apostles, and I want the person
to study the icon and just look

00:50:37.410 --> 00:50:39.990
around it and see what's going on.

00:50:39.990 --> 00:50:43.200
Because that's one of the
reasons icons were first done,

00:50:43.200 --> 00:50:46.770
to educate people who
could not read.

00:50:46.770 --> 00:50:50.440
Most people could not read back
then, and so is telling the story.

00:50:50.440 --> 00:50:56.590
It's illustrating a story, and
today, in the Orthodox churches,

00:50:56.590 --> 00:51:00.690
we have a front to stand that's
full of icons, the Last Supper,

00:51:00.690 --> 00:51:06.470
the apostles, Jesus, St. Mary,
the Archangel, et cetera,

00:51:06.470 --> 00:51:12.150
and so that's really the main
element, telling the story.

00:51:12.150 --> 00:51:15.380
Why is St. George on a horse?

00:51:15.380 --> 00:51:16.930
He's killing the Dragon.

00:51:16.930 --> 00:51:18.930
What is the Dragon?

00:51:18.930 --> 00:51:20.730
Evil, the devil.

00:51:20.730 --> 00:51:25.000
And let's say one of a monk.

00:51:25.000 --> 00:51:30.220
Well, why is he standing there
holding the cane the way he's

00:51:30.220 --> 00:51:31.520
doing it?

00:51:31.520 --> 00:51:32.820
Why is he standing there --

00:51:32.820 --> 00:51:38.360
why is he wearing something
different than another monk?

00:51:38.360 --> 00:51:42.730
It's telling the story, and that's
really the elements important

00:51:42.730 --> 00:51:44.330
to me for an icon.

00:51:44.330 --> 00:51:49.630
It's telling the story, and it has
to look nice to hold the attention.

00:51:49.630 --> 00:51:55.850
Somebody once said to me that you
try to make your icons too pretty.

00:51:55.850 --> 00:52:00.170
That's not Coptic, and
by the way, several monks

00:52:00.170 --> 00:52:04.410
and bishops said don't
listen to him, Evelyn.

00:52:04.410 --> 00:52:09.680
But I have seen icons
that are done carelessly,

00:52:09.680 --> 00:52:11.290
and to me, you lose your story.

00:52:11.290 --> 00:52:12.750
You lose the attention.

00:52:12.750 --> 00:52:17.300
Once you lose the person viewing
it, and they're thinking, wow,

00:52:17.300 --> 00:52:19.400
she looks like she has a mustache.

00:52:19.400 --> 00:52:21.660
You've lost telling the story.

00:52:21.660 --> 00:52:24.630
And maybe the story was
something that was going

00:52:24.630 --> 00:52:26.650
to get the person closer to God.

00:52:26.650 --> 00:52:31.910
So it has to be attractive,
and it has to tell a story.

00:52:31.910 --> 00:52:33.520
Anything else?

00:52:33.520 --> 00:52:34.820
Yes?

00:52:34.820 --> 00:52:38.180
&gt;&gt; How are the icons consecrated?

